limbs.label: 3 Part Stroke with Foot
limbs.description: This is the same as Bone with Foot except that the three sections of the limb are all separate paths in the limb layer, so you can style them independently.If you don’t want the foot, simply delete the Foot Group from the limb layer.

limbs.label: Colored Stroke
limbs.description: This limb replicates the color, split and rounding controls of a Taper, in a stroke limb. You can still use Curvature to round out the joint, and everything is based on stroked paths instead of filled shapes. There is a single control to set the Stroke Width.

limbs.label: Faux 3D Sleeve
limbs.description: This is based on Faux 3D Stroke but has an open appearance to the sleeve end.

limbs.label: Faux 3D Stroke
limbs.description: This Bone adds a Faux 3D look using two strokes with Trim Paths.It uses the Start and End Sizes, Colors, Lower Split and Lower Rounding properties in the Limber effect.This limb only works as expected when the End Size is smaller than the Start Size.

limbs.label: Offset Stroke
limbs.description: This limb is designed for cases where you want to offset a bone path on one side only, eg. for a stripe on one side of a leg.There are controls on the limb layer for the amount of offset and subdivision (smoothness) of the path. It gets more CPU-intensive as you increase the subdivision.  You may want to reduce the subdivision until you come to render.Tip: if you don’t want bendiness, try setting Bone Curvature to 0.1 and reduce the Offset Path Subdivision to 2.

limbs.label: Outlined Stroke
limbs.description: This limb provides three, separate outlined strokes, with width, color and split controls. The outline stroke retains it’s width even when you scale up the limb. It only works as expected when the Sizes are smaller towards the end.

limbs.label: Stroke for adding strokes
limbs.description: This limb adds a second stroke which is expression-linked back to the base path so it runs faster. It has a Trim Paths and different stroke properties. You can duplicate this group and change each copy.

limbs.label: Stroke with End Rounding
limbs.description: This limb adds faux-3D rounding to the start and end caps of the stroke that you can animate for an illusion of depth.

limbs.label: Stroke with Foot
limbs.description: This limb adds a fourth point to the end of the path, like a foot, with controls for length, and tangent angles so you can simulate toe and heel roll.

limbs.label: Tapered Stroke
limbs.description: This limb does a fair job of combining the features of a Taper (colors, widths, splits) with a Stroke limb (curvature). It only works as expected when the Sizes are smaller towards the end.

limbs.label: Expanded Splits
limbs.description: See controls on the limb layer to change the expansion.

limbs.label: Foot with Toes
limbs.description: See controls on the limb layer to alter the foot.

limbs.label: Hand
limbs.description: Alter the shapes inside the limb layer’s Hand Group to suit your needs. This group rotates as if it were parented to a locator. The hand group will not flip with the Clockwise property (use Simple Foot if you need that).

limbs.label: Kurts Elbow Crease
limbs.description: This limb is based on Kurt’s Elbow Crease but adds a wider T-shirt style split in the upper limb. There are controls on the limb layer to adjust the sleeve size.Upper Rounding is ignored in this limb.

limbs.label: Legacy Taper
limbs.description: The Middle Width cannot be larger than the largest of the other two widths.

limbs.label: Half Taper
limbs.description: This limb is intended for use as a matte - check out the Orphaned Limb Layers section of the User Guide to do so.Some properties such as Rounding and Colors are ignored in this limb.

limbs.label: Outlined Arm
limbs.description: The Middle Width cannot be larger than the largest of the other two widths.

limbs.label: Round Corners Taper
limbs.description: This limb is based on Square Elbow, but uses Round Corners to smooth the shape.The Middle Width cannot be larger than the largest of the other two widths.

limbs.label: Square Elbow
limbs.description: The Middle Width cannot be larger than the largest of the other two widths.

limbs.label: Swept Elbow
limbs.description: You can adjust the inside and outside edges independently, from straight lines like ‘Square Elbow’ to fully curved like ‘Curved Bezier Taper’. This limb has has three width properties, and one color.
